<h1 id="wb-cont">COVID-19: Financial help if you are outside Canada</h1>


<p>The Government of Canada created the COVID-19 Emergency Loan Program for Canadians Abroad as a temporary financial assistance program to help Canadians travelling outside Canada to return home or to shelter in place while they arrange to return to Canada. </p>
<p>
You can apply for an emergency repayable loan if you have no other available source of funds to return home, such as: 
<ul>
	<li>credit cards</li>
	<li>banks</li>
	<li>insurance providers</li>
	<li>money transfers from friends and family</li>
</ul>
</p>
<p>To be eligible to apply, you must:
  <ul>
	<li>be outside Canada</li>
	<li>be a Canadian citizen (Canadian permanent residents may be eligible in some instances. Please review the <a href="https://travel.gc.ca/assistance/emergency-info/financial-assistance/covid-19-financial-help-faqs">FAQs</a> for more information on eligibility)</li>
	<li>have no available source of funds</li>
	<li>have had plans in place to return to Canada before COVID-19 that have been disrupted by the COVID-19 pandemic</li>
</ul>  
</p>
<p>This emergency repayable loan of up to $5,000 will cover your short-term needs while you work toward returning home and the costs of your travel back to Canada.  Each application is assessed according to the applicant’s specific situation and needs.</p>

<h2>How to apply</h2>

<p>Please review the <a href="https://travel.gc.ca/assistance/emergency-info/financial-assistance/covid-19-financial-help-faqs">Frequently asked questions</a> page for information on eligibility criteria and eligible costs. </p>

<p>If you are outside Canada, are eligible, and need financial assistance, contact the <a href="/assistance/embassies-consulates">nearest Government of Canada office</a> or Global Affairs Canada’s Emergency Watch and Response Centre in Ottawa at +1 613-996-8885 (call collect where available) or <a href="mailto:CAN.finances.CV19@international.gc.ca">CAN.finances.CV19@international.gc.ca</a>.</p>


<p>You may be asked to provide copies of the following documents to show that you had clear plans to return to Canada before COVID-19:
 <ul>
	<li>a confirmed travel itinerary</li>
	<li>a temporary visa for a foreign country (tourism, business, student, work) with a clear end date</li>
</ul> 
</p>

<h2>
    How to repay the loan
</h2>
<p>If you have received a COVID-19 emergency loan, an invoice and instructions on how to repay it will be sent to the email address you used in your application. </p>
<p>This loan must be paid back to Global Affairs Canada. We will take collection measures if you have not repaid the loan within 180 days of the invoice date. </p>
